cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CY 

This paper is about the development of a language server for the OCaml programming language, which involves topics related to programming languages (cs.PL), software engineering (cs.SE), machine learning (cs.LG), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and cybernetics (cs.CY). The focus of the paper is on the design and implementation of the language server, which involves adapting existing tools to better support incrementality, incompleteness, and error handling. The paper also discusses the challenges of building good editor support for expressive programming languages and frustrating tooling ecosystems, which are relevant to software engineering and computational linguistics.
